<emphasis id="B914EAFD13681641236AD7C8FDE22DA0" box="[381,636,1967,1988]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Triumfetta decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B914EAFD13681641209DD7D7FCFD2DA0" box="[650,867,1967,1989]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">K.N.L. Alves et al. 244</emphasis>
- MG).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF1F6667136F1646229FD57DFAB72F54" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541550" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6541550" box="[136,1321,1306,1328]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541550/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" startId="4.[136,229,1306,1328]" targetBox="[151,1391,216,1245]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BDF36EF136F1646229FD57DFAB72F54" blockId="4.[136,1321,1306,1328]" box="[136,1321,1306,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F1646229FD57DFF602F4B" bold="true" box="[136,254,1306,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
Map of 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F16462358D57DFDD02F4B" box="[335,590,1306,1327]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decaglandulata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F16462358D57DFDD02F4B" box="[335,590,1306,1327]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Triumfetta decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(red-dot) distribution in Serra dos Martírios-Andorinhas, Pará State, Brazil.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDF36EF136F164622AAD539FD282CD8" blockId="4.[136,1452,1374,2085]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164622AAD539FE4E2F1C" bold="true" box="[189,464,1374,1400]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Conservation status:—</emphasis>
The new species was found at APA Araguaia, in a pasture area, by the roadside. Despite being placed at a conservation unit, the area suffers intense anthropic stress, with agribusiness expansion. Only one sample of 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F1646232FD5C1FDFB2FA4" box="[312,613,1446,1472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decaglandulata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F1646232FD5C1FDFB2FA4" box="[312,613,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Triumfetta decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected and it was impossible to obtain information of its extent of occurrence (EOO) and area of occupancy (AOO). The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F1646216CD5ADFC6E2F80" box="[891,1008,1482,1508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F1646216CD5ADFC6E2F80" box="[891,1008,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Triumfetta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="F377767F136F16462705D5ADFAC72F80" box="[1298,1369,1482,1508]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and it is often present in open areas, but few specimens are represented in herbaria. Thus, this lack of distribution data frequently affects the conservation status assessment of the species. According to the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (2012), 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F16462366D651FD022C34" box="[369,668,1590,1616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decaglandulata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F16462366D651FD022C34" box="[369,668,1590,1616]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Triumfetta decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered as Data Deficient (DD) because only the typespecimen is known and appropriate data on abundance and/or distribution are unknown. However, we emphasize that its natural habitat located at APA Araguaia is under anthropic impact, and therefore, attention should be redirected to the preservation of this unique known population.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37A6564136F164722AAD6A1FAB92844" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="292" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDF36EF136F164622AAD6A1FA102C84" blockId="4.[136,1452,1374,2085]" box="[189,1422,1734,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164622AAD6A1FEFA2C84" bold="true" box="[189,356,1734,1760]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F164623E1D6A1FD3A2C84" box="[502,676,1734,1760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decaglandulata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164623E1D6A1FD3A2C84" box="[502,676,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the ten glands observed in the species’ androgynophore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36EF136F164622AAD68DFE4E2D14" blockId="4.[136,1452,1374,2085]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164622AAD68DFE4A2D60" bold="true" box="[189,468,1770,1796]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Taxonomic affinities:—</emphasis>
According to the classification by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136F16462145D68CFC4F2D61" author="Lay, K. K." box="[850,977,1770,1797]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" pagination="315 - 395" refId="ref3779" refString="Lay, K. K. (1950) The American species of Triumfetta L. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 37: 315 - 395. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2394513" type="journal article" year="1950">Lay (1950)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F164621CBD68CFB3B2D60" box="[988,1189,1770,1796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decaglandulata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164621CBD68CFB3B2D60" box="[988,1189,1770,1796]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">T. decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits the 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F164626E9D68DFE842D4C" authority="DC." authorityName="DC." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Lappula">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164626E9D68DFAED2D60" box="[1278,1395,1770,1796]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Triumfetta</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F1646229FD769FF7B2D4C" box="[136,229,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Lappula</emphasis>
DC.
</taxonomicName>
based on its rigid spines, as well as the series 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F1646210BD768FBFA2D4C" authority="Sprague &amp; Hutch." authorityName="Sprague &amp; Hutch." box="[796,1124,1806,1832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Uncinatae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F1646210BD768FC0F2D4C" box="[796,913,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Uncinatae</emphasis>
Sprague &amp; Hutch.
</taxonomicName>
, based on its uncinate spines. The new species is mainly featured by the ten glands on the androgynophore and by the absence of membranaceous urceolus and petals (
<figureCitation id="135B2A6A136F16462379D731FE5C2D14" box="[366,450,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[187,1414,212,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[151,1436,187,1952]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Illustration of Triumfetta decaglandulata: A. Habit. B. Detail of the leaf base. C. Inflorescence. D. Flower. E. Sepals. F. Glands on the androgynophore and ovary. G. Cross section of the ovary (A-G based on K.N.L. Alves et al 244; Drawn by Alex Pinheiro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541546/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36EF136F164622AAD71CFE7A2240" blockId="4.[136,1452,1374,2085]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">
Most of 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F1646230BD71DFE0F2DF0" box="[284,401,1914,1940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F1646230BD71DFE0F2DF0" box="[284,401,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Triumfetta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have pentamerous flowers and five glands on the androgynophore (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136F1646269DD71DFB672DF1" author="Lay, K. K." box="[1162,1273,1914,1941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" pagination="315 - 395" refId="ref3779" refString="Lay, K. K. (1950) The American species of Triumfetta L. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 37: 315 - 395. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2394513" type="journal article" year="1950">Lay 1950</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136F16462712D71DFA012DF0" author="Halford, D. A." box="[1285,1439,1914,1940]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" pagination="495 - 587" refId="ref3555" refString="Halford, D. A. (1997) Notes on Tiliaceae in Australia: A revision of the genus Triumfetta L. Austrobaileya 4: 495 - 587." type="journal article" year="1997">Halford 1997</bibRefCitation>
), except for 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F164622E9D7F9FAAE2DDC" authority="Gonzalez-Martinez, J. Jimenez Ram. &amp; Rios-Carrasco (2016: 273)" authorityName="Gonzalez-Martinez, J. Jimenez Ram. &amp; Rios-Carrasco" authorityPageNumber="273" authorityYear="2016" box="[254,1328,1950,1977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acahuizotlanensis">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164622E9D7F9FDDC2DDC" box="[254,578,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Triumfetta acahuizotlanensis</emphasis>
González-Martínez, J. Jiménez Ram. &amp; Rios-Carrasco (2016: 273)
</taxonomicName>
, which has tetramerous flowers and four glands (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136F16462030D7A5FCF32DB9" author="Jimenez-Ramirez, J. &amp; Gonzalez-Martinez, C. A. &amp; Rios-Carrasco, S." box="[551,877,1986,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" pagination="273 - 278" refId="ref3683" refString="Jimenez-Ramirez, J., Gonzalez-Martinez, C. A. &amp; Rios-Carrasco, S. (2016) Triumfetta acahuizotlanensis (Malvaceae), a new tree species endemic of Guerrero, Mexico. Phytotaxa 265: 273 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 265.3.8" type="journal article" year="2016">
Jiménez-Ramírez 
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164620E4D7A4FCB52DB8" box="[755,811,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
), as well as for 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F1646260FD7A4FB172DB8" box="[1048,1161,1986,2012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lappula">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F1646260FD7A4FB172DB8" box="[1048,1161,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">T. lappula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is the only species lacking glands (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136F1646232AD781FE312265" author="Lay, K. K." box="[317,431,2022,2049]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" pagination="315 - 395" refId="ref3779" refString="Lay, K. K. (1950) The American species of Triumfetta L. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 37: 315 - 395. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2394513" type="journal article" year="1950">Lay 1950</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F164623D3D780FD0E2264" box="[452,656,2022,2048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decaglandulata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164623D3D780FD0E2264" box="[452,656,2022,2048]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">T. decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only known species belonging to genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136F164626BCD781FABE2264" box="[1195,1312,2022,2048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136F164626BCD781FABE2264" box="[1195,1312,2022,2048]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Triumfetta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that has ten glands on the androgynophore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36EF136E164722AAD0F9FA342BF5" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E164722AAD0F9FE772ADC" box="[189,489,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decaglandulata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E164722AAD0F9FE772ADC" box="[189,489,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Triumfetta decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess absent petals, character also shared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E16472637D0F8FB0D2ADC" box="[1056,1171,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lappula">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E16472637D0F8FB0D2ADC" box="[1056,1171,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">T. lappula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E164726DAD0F8FE912AB9" authority="Halford (1997: 543)" authorityName="Halford" authorityPageNumber="543" authorityYear="1997" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E164726DAD0F8FAD22ADC" box="[1229,1356,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">T. centralis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136E16472743D0F9FE912AB9" author="Halford, D. A." pageId="5" pageNumber="292" pagination="495 - 587" refId="ref3555" refString="Halford, D. A. (1997) Notes on Tiliaceae in Australia: A revision of the genus Triumfetta L. Austrobaileya 4: 495 - 587." type="journal article" year="1997">Halford (1997: 543)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E1647230BD0A5FCAB2AB9" authority="(Domin) Halford (1997: 562)" authorityName="Halford" authorityPageNumber="562" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Domin" box="[284,821,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E1647230BD0A5FE7E2AB8" box="[284,480,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Triumfetta albida</emphasis>
(Domin) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136E16472046D0A5FCAB2AB9" author="Halford, D. A." box="[593,821,194,221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" pagination="495 - 587" refId="ref3555" refString="Halford, D. A. (1997) Notes on Tiliaceae in Australia: A revision of the genus Triumfetta L. Austrobaileya 4: 495 - 587." type="journal article" year="1997">Halford (1997: 562)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E1647217AD0A4FAA72AB9" authority="Halford (1997: 562)" authorityName="Halford" authorityPageNumber="562" authorityYear="1997" box="[877,1337,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipedunculata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E1647217AD0A4FBD32AB8" box="[877,1101,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">T. longipedunculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136E16472641D0A5FAA72AB9" author="Halford, D. A." box="[1110,1337,194,221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" pagination="495 - 587" refId="ref3555" refString="Halford, D. A. (1997) Notes on Tiliaceae in Australia: A revision of the genus Triumfetta L. Austrobaileya 4: 495 - 587." type="journal article" year="1997">Halford (1997: 562)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also have absent petals or, when present, often inconspicuous. Although the new species and 
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E16472650D080FB5E2B64" box="[1095,1216,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E16472650D080FB222B64" box="[1095,1212,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lappula">T. lappula</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
are registered in the Americas, 
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E16472314D16CFE652B40" box="[259,507,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E16472314D16CFEF72B40" authorityName="Halford" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Domin" box="[259,361,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albida">T. albida</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E16472361D16CFE662B40" authorityName="Halford" authorityYear="1997" box="[374,504,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centralis">T. centralis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E16472022D16CFC8B2B40" authorityName="Halford" authorityYear="1997" box="[565,789,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipedunculata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E16472022D16CFC8B2B40" box="[565,789,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">T. longipedunculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in 
<collectingCountry id="F377767F136E16472197D16DFC742B40" box="[896,1002,266,292]" name="Australia" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Australia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E164721E1D16DFB252B40" authorityName="Halford" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Domin" box="[1014,1211,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E164721E1D16DFB252B40" box="[1014,1211,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Triumfetta albida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species by the presence of 30 or more stamens (vs. 10-12 stamens) and ovary 2-celled (vs. ovary 6-celled). 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E16472720D149FF742B08" authorityName="Halford" authorityYear="1997" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E16472720D149FF742B08" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Triumfetta centralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs by the ovary 2-celled (vs. ovary 6-celled), and the toothed stigma (vs. bifid stigma). 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E16472720D135FED22BF4" authorityName="Halford" authorityYear="1997" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipedunculata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E16472720D135FED22BF4" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Triumfetta longipedunculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the presence of ca. 60 stamens (vs. 10-12 stamens) and 3-lobed stigma (vs. bifid stigma).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36EF136E164722AAD1FDFAB92844" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E164722AAD1FDFE762BD0" box="[189,488,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decaglandulata">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E164722AAD1FDFE762BD0" box="[189,488,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Triumfetta decaglandulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E1647207FD1FCFD452BD0" box="[616,731,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lappula">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E1647207FD1FCFD452BD0" box="[616,731,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">T. lappula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in stem indument and leaf shape, lack of petals and geographic distribution – both species are recorded in 
<collectingRegion id="49A4F80D136E1647204FD1D9FD542BBC" box="[600,714,446,472]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Pará State</collectingRegion>
, Northern 
<collectingCountry id="F377767F136E16472129D1D9FC182BBC" box="[830,902,446,472]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. However, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D6C136E16472688D1D8FA912BBC" box="[1183,1295,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Triumfetta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lappula">
<emphasis id="B914EAFD136E16472688D1D8FA912BBC" box="[1183,1295,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">T. lappula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it has 10-12 stamens (vs. 15 stamens), ovary 6-celled (vs. 2-celled), ten glands on the androgynophore (vs. androgynophore absent) and lack of membranaceous urceolus (vs. inconspicuous urceolus) (see Gual-Díaz &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B1E136E1647268ED261FA852844" author="Perez" box="[1177,1307,518,544]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" pagination="33 - 96" refId="ref3511" refString="Gual-Diaz &amp; Perez (2018) Diversity of subfamilies Grewioideae and Tilioideae (Malvaceae) in the state of Guerrero, Mexico. Acta Botanica Mexicana 122: 33 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.21829 / abm 122.2018.1161." type="journal article" year="2018">Pérez 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
